本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:黃薇靜研究生(外文):HUANG,WEI-JING論文名稱:簡媜老年書寫研究論文名稱(外文):The Study of Jian Zhen’s Elderly Writing指導教授:吳盈靜指導教授(外文):WU,YING-JING學位類別:碩士校院名稱:國立嘉義大學系所名稱:中國文學系研究所學門:人文學門學類:中國語文學類畢業學年度:103語文別:中文論文頁數:246中文關鍵詞:簡媜、老年書寫、生老病死、《誰在銀閃閃的地方，等你》外文關鍵詞:Jian Zhen、Elderly Writing、Illness and death、“Who Is Waiting for You at The Glimmering Place”相關次數:

被引用:2點閱:531評分:下載:92書目收藏:1



    簡媜，當代散文大家，從1985年初作《水問》以來，迄今仍然筆耕不輟，創作質量相當可觀，二十八年來已出版了二十本散文集，在台灣當代散文史上具有一定的標竿意義與重要位置。2013年《誰在銀閃閃的地方》一書的出版，更創造了她散文書寫的高峰，她以獨特的簡式幽默，細膩的情思，豐富的個人經驗與知識取材，真誠地在漸老之年自剖、自嘲、自省而不自憐，完整而有系統地洞察了自己與他人生命裡必經的生老病死議題。然而，其實簡媜對於老年議題的關註，在年少時期便能窺見端倪，早期的一些散文篇章便對老年書寫有所闡發，是以本論文撰寫的內容與範圍，便是以簡媜歷年來散文集中，與老年書寫相關的篇章做深入的探討。    首先由「簡媜的文學人生與生命書寫」的梳理出發，接著綜觀簡媜在老年書寫裡的內容意蘊，其中囊括簡媜老年書寫裡所運用的複合書寫──紀實的生老病死與凋零的老年幻想，最後針對簡媜老年書寫中，獨特的寫作結構方式和敘事方法、語言詞彙運用、靈活的修辭技巧等書寫形式做探討。期能透過縝密的探索與詮釋過程，叩問流金至鎏銀歲月裡的生命議題，抉發他人與個我的生命意義。

    Jian Zhen, a contemporary essayist, has been keeping on writing since she finished her first essay “Water” in 1985. Furthermore, the quantities of her works are considerable. 20 collections of her essays were published over 28 years. Therefore, her works have its certain benchmarking meaning and play an important role in Taiwan contemporary essay history. In addition, the publishing of the book “Who Is Waiting for You at The Glimmering Place” in 2013 created climax of Jian Zhen’s essay writing. She used special humor, delicate emotion, rich personal experience and knowledge to analyze, reflect and make fun of herself genuinely without self-pity while she is getting older. Thus, she observed the illness and death topics between others and herself which people must pass through completely and systematically. However, the Jian Zhen’s focus on elderly writing can be seen a little bit when she was young. In some of her essays before, she has written her thought about elderly writing. Consequently, the content of this thesis is the deeper discussion from Jian Zhen’s recent essays collections about elderly writing.    First, the thesis start with Jian Zhen’s literature lifetime and life writing, then look at the meaning implied in her elderly writing, including the composite writing of real illness, death, and elderly illusion from her elderly writing. Finally, it points out the special writing construction, event describing, words using and flexible rhetorical skill in her elderly writing, and makes a discussion about them. Hope that people can realize the life issues from young to old, and discover the meaning of life between other people and individual through careful explorations and descriptions.

